00:03:34.639 --> 00:03:39.759
What do you typically do when you want to get a better understanding of an algorithm?

00:03:39.759 --> 00:03:45.080
You can read the article, you can study the implementation, or maybe implement it yourself

00:03:45.080 --> 00:03:47.039
from scratch.

00:03:47.039 --> 00:03:51.199
Or you just run it a bunch of times and see what happens.

00:03:51.199 --> 00:03:57.740
So when I say behavior of an algorithm, I'm talking about how the output of that algorithm

00:03:57.740 --> 00:03:59.759
relates to its inputs, right?

00:03:59.759 --> 00:04:05.759
So we have the data, we have the hyperparameters of the algorithm, and the algorithm itself

00:04:05.759 --> 00:04:06.759
of course.

