Well, in the output there are, of course, the predictions, there is often a performance

00:04:13.240 --> 00:04:21.480
metric associated or derived from those predictions, and perhaps there's also some internal statistic.

00:04:21.480 --> 00:04:27.959
You can visualize this statically, or as an animation like I did, or perhaps even interactively

00:04:27.959 --> 00:04:32.519
so that you can play around with the inputs.

