which contains all the links to everything that I talked about,

00:21:01.319 --> 00:21:02.920
you can scan this QR code.

00:21:05.959 --> 00:21:06.520
Yes, sir.

00:21:06.520 --> 00:21:08.040
First, thank you for a great presentation.

00:21:08.599 --> 00:21:12.760
I'm curious about, given the focus on Polaris and data visualization and everything,

00:21:13.959 --> 00:21:15.800
given the recent developments in Polaris,

00:21:15.800 --> 00:21:18.199
where there now is also a data visualization backend,

00:21:18.280 --> 00:21:20.680
is that something that has changed the plans for your book

00:21:20.680 --> 00:21:23.880
in how you're going to work with data visualizations and Polaris?

00:21:23.880 --> 00:21:25.640
Or is it going to be used?

00:21:26.280 --> 00:21:28.920
All right, I already see Thijs laughing there in the back.

00:21:29.560 --> 00:21:32.199
You've touched upon a very sensitive topic here.

00:21:32.920 --> 00:21:36.280
And that is that I had already written chapter 16,

00:21:36.280 --> 00:21:41.239
data visualization, when HV plot was the default backend.

00:21:41.239 --> 00:21:42.439
But I should have known better.

00:21:42.439 --> 00:21:45.880
I should have known that this API was unstable

00:21:45.880 --> 00:21:48.040
and that it could change any moment.

00:21:48.040 --> 00:21:51.800
But I was just too excited about using Polaris for plotting.

00:21:52.439 --> 00:21:58.119
And so you can understand that when I first heard from Marco Gorelli

00:21:58.119 --> 00:22:01.560
that the default plotting backend was going to change to Altair,

00:22:01.560 --> 00:22:02.920
that I was not pleased.

00:22:03.479 --> 00:22:05.400
Although, of course, now I totally understand

00:22:05.400 --> 00:22:08.040
why Altair is a better choice for this, right?

00:22:08.040 --> 00:22:10.760
Especially for having this interactive workflow.

00:22:13.319 --> 00:22:16.680
So, and I believe your question was,

00:22:16.680 --> 00:22:19.560
is the change of the visualization backend influencing the book?

00:22:20.280 --> 00:22:21.400
Yes, very practically.

00:22:21.400 --> 00:22:24.119
I have to rewrite chapter 16, yeah?

00:22:24.119 --> 00:22:26.920
So the book is probably delayed by a month.

00:22:28.920 --> 00:22:29.800
Now, it's going to be all right.

00:22:29.800 --> 00:22:33.319
We expected the book to be available somewhere in January.

00:22:33.959 --> 00:22:34.760
Yeah, yeah.

00:22:35.880 --> 00:22:36.439
Hi, Jeroen.

00:22:36.439 --> 00:22:37.000
